Sweden's Telefon AB L.M. Ericsson&lt;ERIC ST> said one of its units won a contract worth 7.5 mlndlrs from the West German PTT, taking the value of orderssigned with the Bundespost in the past few days to 47.5 mlndlrs.    The latest order for Ericsson Information Systems is for2,000 Alfaskop computer terminals to be supplied over thecoming two years, the company said in a statement.    On Tuesday the Ericsson subsidiary announced a 40 mln dlrcontract from the Bundespost to deliver personal computers andrelated equipment. REUTER&#3;